# README Structure

All README files must follow this standard structure:

## 1. Main Title

```markdown
# Project Title
```

- Use a single `#` for the main title
- The title must be descriptive and clear

## 2. Hidden Block (Metadata)

```markdown
<!-- hide -->

By [@user](https://github.com/user) and [other contributors](https://github.com/org/repo/graphs/contributors) at [4Geeks Academy](https://4geeksacademy.com/)

[![build by developers](https://img.shields.io/badge/build_by-Developers-blue)](https://4geeks.com)
[![4Geeks Academy](https://img.shields.io/twitter/follow/4geeksacademy?style=social&logo=x)](https://x.com/4geeksacademy)

🌐 _These guidelines are also [available in English/Spanish](./README.md)_.

**Before you start** / **Antes de empezar**:

> We need you! These exercises are built and maintained collaboratively by people like you. If you find a bug 🐞 or a typo, please contribute and/or report it.

<!-- endhide -->
```

**Required elements:**

- Author and link to contributors
- Badges: "build by developers" and "4Geeks Academy"
- Link to the README in the other language (with appropriate text for the current language)
- Collaboration message with 🐞 emoji

## 3. Separator

```markdown
---
```

## 4. Challenge Section

```markdown
## 🎯 Your challenge / Tu reto
```

- Always use the 🎯 emoji before the title
- English title: "Your challenge" (or "The Challenge")
- Spanish title: "Tu reto" (or "El Reto")
- Include full project context, problem to solve, and key questions

## 5. Content Sections (by project type)

### For Dashboards

```markdown
### What makes a dashboard "good"?

**1️⃣ Top block:** Main outcome indicators (KPIs)
**2️⃣ Middle block:** Drivers (factors that explain the outcome)
**3️⃣ Bottom block:** Operational details (tables/lists, alerts)
```

### For Web Projects

```markdown
### Specifications by view

#### 1) View 1

#### 2) View 2

...
```

## 5. Getting Started Section

```markdown
## 🌱 How to start the project / Cómo iniciar el proyecto
```

- **Required placement:** always after the challenge (and its subsections) and **before** "What you need to do".
- Instructions on how to begin the project (template, Codespaces, clone, etc.).

## 6. "What you need to do" Section

```markdown
## 💻 What you need to do / Qué debes hacer
```

- Include a checklist of main tasks using `- [ ]`
- Include important warnings with `⚠️ **IMPORTANT:**` / `⚠️ **IMPORTANTE:**`

## 7. Evaluation Section

```markdown
## ✅ What we will evaluate / Qué vamos a evaluar
```

- List of evaluation criteria with `- [ ]`
- May include additional notes with `> Note:` / `> Nota:`

## 8. Submission Section

```markdown
## 📦 How to submit this project / Cómo entregar este proyecto
```

- Clear instructions on what to submit

## 9. Footer

```markdown
---

This and many other projects are built by students as part of the [Coding Bootcamps](https://4geeksacademy.com/) at 4Geeks Academy. Find out more about [Full-Stack Software Developer](https://4geeksacademy.com/en/career-programs/full-stack), [Data Science & Machine Learning](https://4geeksacademy.com/en/career-programs/data-science-ml), [Cybersecurity](https://4geeksacademy.com/en/career-programs/cybersecurity) and [AI Engineering](https://4geeksacademy.com/en/career-programs/ai-engineering).
```

**Required elements:**

- Link to Coding Bootcamps
- List of programs with appropriate links per language
- Spanish README: use `/es/` routes
- English README: use routes without `/es/` or with `/en/` as appropriate

## Additional Rules

1. **Emojis in headings**: Use consistent emojis (🎯, 💻, ✅, 📦, 🌱)
2. **Separators**: Use `---` between major sections
3. **Checklists**: Use `- [ ]` format for tasks and evaluation criteria
4. **Quotes**: Use `>` for quotes and important notes
5. **Images**: Include images when relevant with `![alt](path "title")`
6. **Relative links**: Use relative paths for links between READMEs (`./README.md`)

## Full Structure Example

```markdown
# Project Title

<!-- hide -->

[metadata and badges]

<!-- endhide -->

---

## 🎯 Your challenge

[Challenge content]

---

## 🌱 How to start the project

[Instructions: template, Codespaces, clone, etc.]

---

## 💻 What you need to do

- [ ] Task 1
- [ ] Task 2

---

## ✅ What we will evaluate

- [ ] Criterion 1
- [ ] Criterion 2

---

## 📦 How to submit this project

[Instructions]

---

[Footer with 4Geeks Academy information]
```
